726297f-a.title: Queens: Calamus Avenue - 69th Street
726297f-a.text:
Calamus Ave., south side, east from 69th Street (Cobblestone Road),
showing in the foreground an old roadhouse. It was a hotel in 1880.
Subsequent owners of this place were T. Bennett in 1873 and Mrs. McGowan
in 1891. Bevond the one story house in center of view is Public School
No, 78, which is located on the S.E. Corner of 68th Street and faces on
Maurice Ave., which is a continuation of Calamus Ave.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
